tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE energy_consumption (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    product_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    consumed_energy DECIMAL NOT NULL,
    location VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    date_consumed DATE
);

CREATE TABLE energy_consumption (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  timestamp TIMESTAMP,
  location VARCHAR(100),
  energy_source VARCHAR(50),
  consumption DECIMAL
);

CREATE TABLE optimization_efforts (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  timestamp TIMESTAMP,
  action VARCHAR(100),
  impact DECIMAL,
  efficiency DECIMAL
);

CREATE TABLE EnergyConsumption (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    location VARCHAR(255),
    energy_type VARCHAR(50),
    energy_consumed DECIMAL(10, 2),
    timestamp TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE SupplyChainOptimization (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    optimization_id INT,
    target_location VARCHAR(255),
    optimized_route VARCHAR(255),
    cost_saved DECIMAL(10, 2)
);

CREATE TABLE energy_consumption (
    id INT,
    company_name VARCHAR(255),
    energy_type VARCHAR(50),
    consumption DECIMAL,
    measurement_unit VARCHAR(10)
);

CREATE TABLE supply_chain_optimization (
    id INT,
    company_name VARCHAR(255),
    optimization_technique VARCHAR(50),
    efficiency_rating DECIMAL,
    optimization_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE energy_supplier (
    id INT,
    supplier_name VARCHAR(255),
    contact_name VARCHAR(100),
    contact_email VARCHAR(100),
    phone_number VARCHAR(20)
);

CREATE TABLE supply_chain_location (
    id INT,
    location_name VARCHAR(255),
    address TEXT,
    city VARCHAR(100),
    country VARCHAR(100)
);

CREATE TABLE shipment_details (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  shipment_id INT,
  sender TEXT,
  receiver TEXT,
  shipment_date DATE
);
